Robeta's Pizza Dough

153g 00 flour (1c + 1 tbsp)
153g ap flour (1c + 1 tbsp + 2 tsp)
8g fine sea salt (1 tsp)
2g active dry yeast (3/4 tsp)
4g evoo (1 tsp)

In a large mixing bowl, combine flours and salt/ In a small mixing bowl, stir together 200g (<1c) lukewarm tap water, yeast, and evoo, then pour it into flours. Knead with your hands until well combined, ~3min, then let rest for 15min. Knead rested dough for 3min. Cut into 2 equal pieces and shape each into a ball. Place on heavily floured surface, cover with dampened cloth, and let rest and rise for 3-4hrs at room temp, or 8-24hrs in refrigerator. If refrigerating, remove it 30-45 min before you begin to shape for pizza. To make pizza, place each dough ball on a heavily floured surface and use your fingers to stretch it, then your hands to shape it into rounds. Top and bake.
